# Phase 6 Implementation Plan — Community & Advanced Studio

## Goals
1.  **Community Interaction**: Allow creators to post text updates, polls, and images to engage with subscribers (YouTube "Community Tab" style).
2.  **Advanced Studio**: Expand the Dashboard into a full "Studio" experience with deeper analytics and content management.
3.  **Playlist Management**: Create a dedicated UI for viewing and managing playlists.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Community Tab ([app/channel/[username]/community/page.tsx](file:///C:/GoLive/app/channel/[username]/community/page.tsx))
-   **Feed**: A scrollable list of "Posts".
-   **Post Types**:
    -   **Text**: Simple status updates.
    -   **Poll**: Interactive voting (mocked).
    -   **Image**: Visual updates.
-   **Interactions**: Like and Comment on posts.

### 2. Studio Expansion ([app/studio/page.tsx](file:///C:/GoLive/app/studio/page.tsx))
-   **Content Page**: A data-rich table with filtering (Public/Private, Date range).
-   **Analytics Page**: Interactive charts (Recharts or mocked SVG) showing "Realtime views", "Audience retention".
-   **Comments Manager**: A dedicated inbox for replying to comments.

### 3. Playlist UI ([app/playlist/[id]/page.tsx](file:///C:/GoLive/app/playlist/[id]/page.tsx))
-   **Layout**: Split view (Left: Playlist Info/Cover, Right: Video List).
-   **Features**: "Play All", "Shuffle", drag-and-drop reordering (visual only).

## Verification
-   Go to a channel's Community tab and interact with a poll.
-   Visit the Studio and see the mock analytics graphs.
-   Open a playlist and see the dedicated view.
